events.name: New York Knicks at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored a season-high 36 points on his 28th birthday, and the New York Knicks extended their win streak against the Detroit Pistons to 11 games with a 140-110 victory on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Julius Randle scores 36 as Knicks rout Pistons 140-110

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Tim Hardaway Jr. had to watch when his Dallas Mavericks lost to the Golden State Warriors in last season's Western Conference finals.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavs edge Curry, Warriors in West finals replay

events.name: LA Clippers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Norman Powell scored 22 of his 32 points in the fourth quarter, and the Los Angeles Clippers beat Anfernee Simons and the Portland Trail Blazers 118-112 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Powell scores 32 as Clippers rally past Blazers 118-112
